                                <date>1958</date>. С. <biblScope unit="page">??–??</biblScope>.</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><xi:include href="../encodingdesc.xml" parse="xml"/></teiHeader><text><body><entry xml:id="entry_ʒwap6p9" xml:lang="os"><form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>ʒwap(p)</orth></form><form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>ʒiwap(p)</orth></form><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>ответ</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>answer</q></abv:tr></sense><re><form type="lemma"><orth>ʒwap dæddyn</orth></form><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>отвечать</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>answer (v.)</q></abv:tr></sense></re><abv:exampleGrp><abv:example><quote>īsty ʒwapp yssar</quote><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>найди какой-нибудь ответ</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>find any answer</q></abv:tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>106</biblScope></bibl></abv:example><abv:example><quote>ʒiwapp feǧosgæj ærbamæstgun uj</quote><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>услышав ответ, она вспыхивает</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>she blushes once she has heard the answer</q></abv:tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ОЭп."/><biblScope>61%l280%l</biblScope></bibl></abv:example></abv:exampleGrp><etym xml:lang="ru">Из <mentioned xml:lang="ar" extralang="fa"><lang/> <w>ǰavab</w> <gloss><q>ответ</q></gloss></mentioned>. Ср. <mentioned xml:lang="trk"><lang/> <w>ǯavap</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="trk"><w>ǯuvap</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="trk"><w>ǯevap</w></mentioned>. Бытует в ряде кавказских языков: <mentioned xml:lang="av"><lang/> <w>žavap</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="lez"><lang/> <w>ǯuwab</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ce"><lang/> <w>ǯuap</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kbd"><lang/> <w>žäuap</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-crc"><lang/> <w>ǯäuap</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="lzz"><lang/> <w>ǯevabi</w></mentioned> и др.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>9</biblScope></bibl>.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">From <mentioned xml:lang="ar" extralang="fa"><lang/> <w>ǰavab</w> <gloss><q>answer</q></gloss></mentioned>. Cf. <mentioned xml:lang="trk"><lang/> <w>ǯavap</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="trk"><w>ǯuvap</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="trk"><w>ǯevap</w></mentioned>. The word is found in a number of Caucasian languages: <mentioned xml:lang="av"><lang/> <w>žavap</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="lez"><lang/> <w>ǯuwab</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ce"><lang/> <w>ǯuap</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kbd"><lang/> <w>žäuap</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-crc"><lang/> <w>ǯäuap</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="lzz"><lang/> <w>ǯevabi</w></mentioned> etc.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>9</biblScope></bibl>.</etym></entry></body></text></TEI>